# Component Patterns

## ui/ vs features/

| Directory | Purpose | Examples |
|-----------|---------|---------|
| `components/ui/` | Stateless primitives, no business logic | `Button`, `Card`, `NavCard`, `ArticleCard` |
| `components/features/` | Stateful feature components | `PollGame`, `UXToggle`, `NoodlingCanvas` |
| `components/illustrations/` | `IllustrationSpot` wrapper only | — |

## The UX Toggle System

- `useUXMode` context: exposes `mode` (`"good"` | `"bad"`) and `toggleMode()`
- **Good UX mode:** warm, crafted default experience
- **Bad UX mode:** intentionally terrible (Comic Sans, neon, popups, autoplay)
- Bad UX components live in `components/features/bad-ux/` — mounted/unmounted by context
- Bad UX tokens come from the `badUx` group in `tokens.json`
- Toggle transition should be smooth and satisfying

## Illustration Placeholder System

- Use `<IllustrationSpot name="hero-campfire" />` — takes a `name` prop
- Renders a gradient shimmer until the real asset exists at `/public/illustrations/{name}.png`
- No code changes needed when the real art drops in — just add the file

## Token Usage in Components

```tsx
// Correct — uses CSS custom property
<div className="bg-[var(--color-cream)] text-[var(--semantic-text)]">

// Wrong — naked hardcoded value
<div className="bg-[#f5e6d0]">
```

## Framer Motion

- Use for all animations — see `animation-patterns.mdc` for specifics
- Always wrap animated values with `prefers-reduced-motion` check
- Import from `"framer-motion"` (not `"motion/react"`)
